HEADWORD: Voltzite
<hw>Voltz"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named in honor
of <etsep>Voltz</etsep>, a French engineer.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>An oxysulphide of lead occurring in implanted spherical globules of
